<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bolas Bonesmith</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-23 17:55:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Yet another reason to train more than just 2H Slash... <BR>
I think you'll see the good shadowknights are keeping<BR>
their skills up in all the different weapon skills.<BR>
At level 28, I am at skill 140 in 2h slash, skill 80+ in <BR>
each of piercing, 1h slash, and 2h bash.  You never know<BR>
what good sk weapon you will find, after all.<BR>
<BR>
For training, I like to use fast weapons with good ratios.<BR>
I think that the low delay will give more opportunities to<BR>
increase the skill.  Even better if you can get an enchanter<BR>
to cast quickness on you -- you can see a skill go up three<BR>
times in a single combat sometimes!<BR>
<BR>
Since I play on Vallon Zek, a team pvp server, I favor the <BR>
Rage War Maul for 2h bash due to the +15 vs. magic.  It's <BR>
16 dam 46 del.  Everyone thinks I'm a shaman.  lol.<BR>
<BR>
For 2h slash, the Runic Caver is about your best bet before <BR>
level 30, with it's 18 dam 37 delay.  But I traded it, so <BR>
I'm using my Dark Reaver with 20 dam 42 delay, which should<BR>
proc at level 25 but doesn't actually proc until level 30.<BR>
<BR>
For 1h slash, I like the Bladed Thulian Claws -- quick, and<BR>
they look cool.  5 damage 19 delay.<BR>
<BR>
For piercing, I'm using a Shark Tooth.  A mighty fine weapon<BR>
if you can get one.  5 damage 18 delay -- even speedier than<BR>
the claws!<BR>
<BR>
With the one handed weapons, I like the shiny brass shield<BR>
due to it's low price, decent AC, and +10 vs. magic. I would<BR>
use a Bark Shield if I could get one, due to the higher AC<BR>
and the sweet boost to agility.  Sigh.  Anyone wanna<BR>
trade me one?<BR>
<BR>
I favor a Darkwood Compound Bow in the ranged slot rather<BR>
than a Runed Bone Fork.  I like the kiting ability for<BR>
shadowknights better than the bonus resistances.  In fact,<BR>
I would probably only use an RBF as a warrior in the off<BR>
hand, to pump resistances and practice dual wield.<BR>
<BR>
Well that's my two cents worth on keeping weapon skills up.<BR>
I wonder how long it will be until I regret not practicing<BR>
1h bash and keeping the enameled mace instead of selling it?</font></td></tr></table>
